### Alumni

*   Main article: [List of Complutense University of Madrid alumni](/List_of_Complutense_University_of_Madrid_alumni)

In recent years, the university's notable alumni include 7 [Nobel Prize recipients](/Nobel_Prize), 18 [Prince of Asturias Awardees](/Prince_of_Asturias_Awards), 7 [Miguel de Cervantes Prize recipients](/Miguel_de_Cervantes_Prize), 10 [ERC grantees](/European_Research_Council), [31] as well as [prime ministers of Spain](/Prime_Minister_of_Spain), [European commissioners](/European_Commissioner), presidents of the [EU Parliament](/EU_Parliament), a [European Council](/European_Council) secretary general, [European Central Bank](/European_Central_Bank) Executive Board members, a [NATO](/NATO) secretary general, a [UNESCO](/UNESCO) director general, an [IMF](/IMF) managing director, members of the [Spanish royalty](/Spanish_royal_family), and various [heads of state](/Head_of_state). Over its seven-century history, the University of Madrid has made profound contributions to the sciences, fine arts, and political leadership. Alumni include distinguished philosophers ([José Ortega y Gasset](/Jos%C3%A9_Ortega_y_Gasset), [Ignatius of Loyola](/Ignatius_of_Loyola), [Thomas of Villanova](/Thomas_of_Villanova)), writers ([Federico García Lorca](/Federico_Garc%C3%ADa_Lorca), [Antonio de Nebrija](/Antonio_de_Nebrija), [Pedro Calderón de la Barca](/Pedro_Calder%C3%B3n_de_la_Barca)), scientists ([Santiago Ramón y Cajal](/Santiago_Ram%C3%B3n_y_Cajal), [Severo Ochoa](/Severo_Ochoa), [Andrés Manuel del Río](/Andr%C3%A9s_Manuel_del_R%C3%ADo), [Ricardo Rubio](/Ricardo_Rubio)), historians ([Juan de Mariana](/Juan_de_Mariana), [Juan Ginés de Sepúlveda](/Juan_Gin%C3%A9s_de_Sep%C3%BAlveda)), military leaders (Don [John of Austria](/John_of_Austria), [Alexander Farnese](/Alexander_Farnese,_Duke_of_Parma)), and foreign dignitaries ([Cardinal Mazarin](/Cardinal_Mazarin), [José Rizal](/Jos%C3%A9_Rizal)).

